qu\u1eadn'') of [[Da Nang]] in the [[South Central Coast]] region of Vietnam. As of 2003 the district had a population of 112,196. The district covers an area of 60&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=\"Statoids\">{{cite web|url=http://www.statoids.com/yvn.html|title=Districts of Vietnam|publisher=Statoids|accessdate=March 20, 2009}}</ref> The district is bounded by ocean to the north and east, the [[Han River (Vietnam)|H\u00e0n River]] to the west, and [[Ng\u0169 H\u00e0nh S\u01a1n District]] to the south. [[S\u01a1n Tr\u00e0 Mountain]] occupies a large portion of the district.\n[[File:Tr\u01b0\u1eddng Ch\u00ednh tr\u1ecb Tp. \u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng.jpg|thumb|left|260px|\u0110\u00e0 N\u1eb5ng Political School]]\n\nThe district is divided into 7 [[Ward (Vietnam)|wards]]:\n*An H\u1ea3i B\u1eafc\n*An H\u1ea3i \u0110\u00f4ng\n*An H\u1ea3i T\u00e2y\n*M\u00e2n Th\u00e1i\n*N\u1ea1i Hi\u00ean \u0110\u00f4ng\n*Ph\u01b0\u1edbc M\u1ef9\n*Th\u1ecd Quang\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|16.116|N|108.277|E|source:viwiki_region:VN|format=dms|display=title}}\n\n{{Districts of South Central Coast}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Son Tra District}}\n[[Category:Districts of Da Nang]]\n\n\n{{DaNang-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Expand Vietnamese|date=March 2009|S\u01a1n Tr\u00e0 (qu\u1eadn)}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = S\u01a1n Tr\u00e0 District\n| settlement_type                 = [[List of urban districts of Vietnam|Urban district]]\n| official_name                   = \n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = Qu\u1eadn S\u01a1n Tr\u00e0\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = Da Nang view from top of Son Tra.jpg\n| imagesize                       = 300px\n| image_caption                   = \n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_shield       