ge]], linking Thakhek and [[Nakhon Phanom]], Thailand, across the river, started in 2009 and was opened on 11 November 2011.\n\nThe city has many French colonial style official buildings, villas, and shops. In 1943, 85% of the population of Thakhek were Vietnamese due to the French policy of encouraging Vietnamese immigrants to Laos.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Stuart-Fox |first1=Martin |title=A History of Laos |date=1997 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-59746-3 |page=51 |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=8VvvevRkX-EC&lpg=PP1&dq=A%20History%20of%20Laos&pg=PA51#v=onepage&q=A%20History%20of%20Laos&f=false |accessdate=15 April 2020 |ref=}}</ref> Remnants of the abortive [[Thakhek-Tan Ap railway]] can be seen in and near the town. The railway would have run between Thakhek and [[T\u00e2n \u1ea4p Railway Station]], [[Qu\u1ea3ng B\u00ecnh Province]], [[Vietnam]] through the [[M\u1ee5 Gi\u1ea1 Pass]]. \n\nWestern scientists first encountered the [[Laotian rock rat]], ''kha nyou'' (Laonastes aenigmamus), in Thakhek's market.\n\n== Climate ==\n\n<div style=\"width:72%\">\n{{Weather box\n|location = Thakhek\n|single line = Yes\n|metric first = Yes\n|Jan high F = 84\n|Feb high F = 87\n|Mar high F = 91\n|Apr high F = 94\n|May high F = 91\n|Jun high F = 88\n|Jul high F = 85\n|Aug high F =86\n|Sep high F = 86\n|Oct high F = 87\n|Nov high F =86\n|Dec high F = 83\n|year high F = 87\n|Jan low F = 56\n|Feb low F = 62\n|Mar low F = 67\n|Apr low F = 72\n|May low F = 75\n|Jun low F = 76\n|Jul low F = 75\n|Aug low F = 75\n|Sep low F = 74\n|Oct low F = 68\n|Nov low F = 64\n|Dec low F = 58\n|year low F = 69\n|Jan precipitation inch = 0.1\n|Feb precipitation inch =1.1\n|Mar precipitation inch = 1.6\n|Apr precipitation inch = 4\n|May precipitation inch = 10.9\n|Jun precipitation inch = 13.2\n|Jul precipitation inch = 22.1\n|Aug precipitation inch = 21.1\n|Sep precipitation inch = 16.1\n|Oct precipitation inch = 2.5\n|Nov precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Dec precipitation inch = 0.3\n|year precipitation inch = 93.4\n|source 1 = Weatherbase <ref name=Weatherbase>{{cite web|url =http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather.php3?s=50194&refer=wikipedia |title =Weatherbase: Historical Weather for Thakhek, Laos|publisher=Weatherbase|year=2011}} Retrieved on 24 November 2011</ref>|date=November 2011\n}}\n</div>\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons}}\n* {{wikivoyage-inline|Thakhek}}\n* [http://laotourism.org/khammouane.htm Destination: Khammouane Province] at laotourism.org\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Districts of South Laos}}\n\n[[Category:Laos\u2013Thailand border crossings]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Khammouane Province]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Mekong River]]\n[[Category:Provincial capitals in Laos]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = {{raise|0.2em|Thakhek}}\n|native_name            = {{lower|0.2em|{{nobold|\u0e97\u0ec8\u0eb2\u0ec1\u0e82\u0e81}}}}\n|native_name_lang       = lo\n|settlement_type        = [[Districts of Laos|District]] & [[List of cities in Laos|municipality]]\n|official_name          = Thakhek District\n|image_skyline          = Khammouane Thakhek2 tango7174.jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Thakhek centre\n|pushpin_map           = Laos\n|pushpin_label_position =\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in Laos\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = Laos\n|subdivision_type1      =[[Provinces of Laos|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1      = [[Khammouane Province]]\n|subdivision_type2      =[[Districts of Laos|District]]\n|subdivision_name2      = [[Thakhek District]]\n|subdivision_type3      = \n|subdivision_name3      = \n|subdivision_type4      = \n|subdivision_name4      =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|established_title      = \n|established_date       = \n|area_total_km2           = \n|population_as_of               = 2020\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_total               =85,000<ref>{{cite web |title=Main Cities by Population in Laos |url=https://www.worldometers.info/world-population/laos-population/ |website=Worldometers |accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref>\n|population_density_km2         =\n|timezone               =  [[Time in Laos|ICT]] \n|utc_offset             = +7\n|coordinates            = {{coord|17|24|N|104|48|E|region:LA-KH|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_ft           =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              =\n}} \n\n'''Thakhek''' ([[Lao language]]: \u0e97\u0ec8\u0eb2\u0ec1\u0e82\u0e81), the capital of [[Khammouane Province]], is a town in south-central [[Laos]] on the [[Mekong River]]. The [[Third Thai\u2013Lao Friendship Bridge]], linking Thakhek and [[Nakhon Phanom]], Thailand, across the river, started in 2009 and was opened on 11 November 2011.\n\nThe city has many French colonial style official buildings, villas, and shops. In 1943, 85% of the population of Thakhek were Vietnamese due to the French policy of encouraging Vietnamese immigrants to Laos.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Stuart-Fox |first1=Martin |title=A History of Laos |date=1997 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=978-0-521-59746-3 |page=51 |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=8VvvevRkX-EC&lpg=PP1&dq=A%20History%20of%20Laos&pg=PA51#v=onepage&q=A%20History%20of%20Laos&f=false |accessdate=15 April 2020 |ref=}}</ref> Remnants of the abortive [[Thakhek-Tan Ap railway]] can be seen in and near the town. The railway would have run between Thakhek and [[T\u00e2n \u1ea4p Railway Station]], [[Qu\u1ea3ng B\u00ecnh Province]], [[Vietnam]] through the [[M\u1ee5 Gi\u1ea1 Pass]]. \n\nWestern scientists first encountered the [[Laotian rock rat]], ''kha nyou'' (Laonastes aenigmamus), in Thakhek's market.\n\n== Climate ==\n\n<div style=\"width:72%\">\n{{Weather box\n|location = Thakhek\n|single line = Yes\n|metric first = Yes\n|Jan high F = 84\n|Feb high F = 87\n|Mar high F = 91\n|Apr high F = 94\n|May high F = 91\n|Jun high F = 88\n|Jul high F = 85\n|Aug high F =86\n|Sep high F = 86\n|Oct high F = 87\n|Nov high F =86\n|Dec high F = 83\n|year high F = 87\n|Jan low F = 56\n|Feb low F = 62\n|Mar low F = 67\n|Apr low F = 72\n|May low F = 75\n|Jun low F = 76\n|Jul low F = 75\n|Aug low F = 75\n|Sep low F = 74\n|Oct low F = 68\n|Nov low F = 64\n|Dec low F = 58\n|year low F = 69\n|Jan precipitation inch = 0.1\n|Feb precipitation inch =1.1\n|Mar precipitation inch = 1.6\n|Apr precipitation inch = 4\n|May precipitation inch = 10.9\n|Jun precipitation inch = 13.2\n|Jul precipitation inch = 22.1\n|Aug precipitation inch = 21.1\n|Sep precipitation inch = 16.1\n|Oct precipitation inch = 2.5\n|Nov precipitation inch = 0.4\n|Dec precipitation inch = 0.3\n|year precipitation inch = 93.4\n|source 1 = Weatherbase <ref name=Weatherbase>\n{{cite web\n|url =http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather.php3?s=50194&refer=wikipedia |title =Weatherbase: Historical Weather for Thakhek, Laos\n|publisher=Weatherbase\n|year=2011\n}}\nRetrieved on November 24, 2011.\n</ref>\n|date=November 2011\n}}\n</div>\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons}}\n* {{wikivoyage-inline|Thakhek}}\n* [http://laotourism.org/khammouane.htm Destination: Khammouane Province] at laotourism.org\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Districts of South Laos}}\n\n[[Category:Laos\u2013Thailand border crossings]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Khammouane Province]]\n[[Category:Populated places on the Mekong River]]\n[[Category:Provincial capitals in Laos]]\n", "name_user": "Seligne", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eClimate", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thakhek"}
